modification_summary.raw_text:
TextBlock(citations=None, text='Here is my analysis of the proposed bill to amend the Consumer Financial Protection Act:

{
    "change_type": "Moderate",
    "summary_of_changes": [
        "Renames an existing unit within the CFPB as the 'Office of Community Affairs'",
        "Assigns new duties to this office related to identifying causes and solutions for under-banked, un-banked, and underserved consumers",
        "Requires the office to submit a report to Congress every 2 years on factors impeding consumer access to banking relationships and recommendations to increase participation"  
    ],
    "legal_impact": "The changes would place greater focus within the CFPB on understanding and addressing the needs of underserved consumers who lack access to traditional banking services. The reporting requirements may lead to new regulatory or legislative proposals to increase financial inclusion.",
    "relevance_score": 6,
    "relevance_explanation": "The bill makes notable changes to the mandate and responsibilities of a CFPB office to emphasize a focus on underserved consumers. However, the immediate legal impact is limited, as the bill does not directly change regulations or impose new requirements on financial institutions.",
    "before_and_after": {
        "before": "The Director shall establish a unit whose functions shall include providing information, guidance, and technical assistance regarding the offering and provision of consumer financial products or services to traditionally underserved consumers and communities.",
        "after": "The Director shall establish a unit to be known as the 'Office of Community Affairs'. The Office of Community Affairs shall--
        (I) lead coordination of research to identify any causes and challenges contributing to the decision of individuals who, and households that, do not initiate or maintain on-going and sustainable relationships with depository institutions...;
        (II) identify subject matter experts within the Bureau to work on the issues identified under subclause (I);
        (III) lead coordination efforts between other Federal departments and agencies to better assess the reasons for the lack of, and help increase the participation of, under-banked, un-banked, and underserved consumers in the banking system; and
        (IV) identify and develop strategies to increase financial education to under-banked, un-banked, and underserved consumers.
        The Office of Community Affairs shall submit a report to Congress, within two years of the date of enactment of this subparagraph and every 2 years thereafter, that identifies any factors impeding the ability of, or limiting the option for, individuals or households to have access to fair, on-going, and sustainable relationships with depository institutions to meet their financial needs, discusses any regulatory, legal, or structural barriers to enhancing participation of under-banked, un-banked, and underserved consumers with depository institutions, and contains recommendations to promote better participation for all consumers with the banking system."
    }
}', type='text')
